defaultThe Cities are though punching below their weight – our second tier cities should be more economically successful compared with cities of similar scale and r
defaulto
defaultle in other European and OECD Co
defaultuntries.  For example just for
default Core C
defaultities to punch their weight at the national average would provide the country with an additional £1.3 billion per annum.
defaultLocal Transport infrastructures require radical improvement to maximise economic growth and support improving quality of life an
defaultd the local environment
default but o
defaultur governan
defaultce and services are fragmented. O
defaultur 
defaultCapital
default 
defaultCity
